{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "2D and 3D convolutional networks pre-trained on action recognition tasks are widely used in research [6,[13][14][15].",
    "Nevertheless, models based on RGB struggle with the variability in video backgrounds.",
    "To address this, some studies [6][7][8][16][17][18] suggest the integration of keypoints with RGB videos.",
    "For instance, SAM-SLR [16] utilises graph convolutional networks (GCNs) to process pre-extracted keypoints, while NLASLR [7],HMA [9] and SignBERT [8] suggest decoding 3D hand keypoints directly from RGB videos.",
    "Inspired by these studies, in our system, we utilise both RGB and pose features for video feature extraction."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "2D and 3D convolutional networks pre-trained on action recognition tasks are widely used in research [6,[13][14][15].",
